<TITLE> McCain, 2 other US senators due on Dec 2 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)--US senator John McCain will arrive in the city on Dec 2 as part of a regional tour, an adviser said Thursday. "Senator McCain and two other US senators will arrive on Dec 2 and leave next day," foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury told bdnews24.com. Senator Joseph Lieberman and Senator Lindsey Graham will accompany Senator McCain who has an adopted daughter from Bangladesh. The adviser said, "We are looking forward to this important visit by three significant US senators." "We also look forward to discussing an important issue lying pending with the us legislators: market access for our manufactures such as ready-made-garments." Iftekhar said, "We will also use the opportunity to show them that Bangladesh is a peaceful polity." They will meet government officials, political party leaders and members of civil society to discuss bilateral issues. McCain, a Republican hopeful who lost the US presidential race to Barack Obama on Nov 4, was elected to the US Senate from Arizona in 1986. Senator Joseph Lieberman has represented Connecticut in the Senate since 1988. He was the Democratic nominee for vice president in 2000. Senator Lindsey Graham has been US Senator for South Carolina since 2002. All three senators are members on the Senate Armed Services Committee, with McCain serving as the ranking member. bd
